OL,6,FAsked whether he would resign if it
OL,7,Fwas clear he'd lost the confidence of
OL,8,Fclubs, Sweeney said it was up to the
OL,9,FRFU board to remove him:
OL,11,F"It's really up to the decision of the
OL,12,Fboard. I believe in the programs we've
OL,13,Fput in place... I would stick out
OL,14,Funless the board said to me otherwise
OL,15,Fand I'm not thinking about the outcome
OL,16,Fof the special general meeting."
